'''Glitches''' in Chrono Trigger include exploits and bugs discovered in various versions.

== Known Glitches ==

=== HP Overflow ===
In some versions:
* Healing past max HP
* Damage calculation errors
* Tab stat boosts

=== Save Anywhere (New Game+) ===
New Game+ preserves:
* All items
* Character stats
* Enables some sequence breaks

== Combat Glitches ==

=== Damage Overflow ===
Extremely high damage calculations:
* Can wrap around to low damage
* Affects certain boss strategies
* Version dependent

=== Status Effect Stacking ===
Some status effects:
* Stack unexpectedly
* Cause unusual combat behavior

== Item Duplication ==

=== SNES Version ===
Item duplication methods exist:
* Specific menu manipulation
* Allows duplicating rare items
* Patched in some versions

=== Equipment Swap ===
During equipment changes:
* Items may duplicate
* Careful timing required

== Sequence Breaking ==

=== Bucket Skip ===
The End of Time bucket:
* Allows early Lavos access
* Used in speedruns
* Intentional design but enables sequence breaks

=== Black Omen Multi-Clear ===
Black Omen can be completed in each era:
* Collect items multiple times
* Not a glitch but exploitable
* Intentional design

== Version-Specific Glitches ==

=== SNES Original ===
* Item duplication
* Certain overflow issues
* Save corruption possible

=== PlayStation (PS1) ===
* Loading time issues (not glitches)
* Some fixes from SNES version

=== Nintendo DS ===
* Most glitches patched
* New content added
* Some new minor issues

=== PC/Mobile ===
* Most issues fixed
* Different input methods
* Minor display issues

== Speedrun Techniques ==

=== Any% Routes ===
* New Game+ with high stats
* Direct Lavos fight
* Minimal story progression

=== 100% Routes ===
* All endings
* All items
* Exploits for efficiency

== Graphical Glitches ==

=== Sprite Issues ===
* Rare sprite corruption
* Usually temporary

=== Animation Errors ===
* Tech animation glitches
* Not game-breaking

== Save File Issues ==

=== Corruption ===
* Rare save corruption
* Battery backup failure (original cartridge)
* Always backup saves

=== Memory Card (PS1) ===
* Standard PS1 save issues
* Not CT-specific

== Tips ==

'''Safe Playing:'''
* Save regularly
* Multiple save slots
* Don't rely on glitches

'''Exploiting Responsibly:'''
* Backup before attempting
* Know your version
* Some glitches are patched

